## Guntherâ€™s â€œCareer Killerâ€ Segment  
- Gunther boasts retiring multiple wrestlers, calls them losers  
- Claims show should celebrate him, not AJ Styles  
- GM ejects Gunther; Dragon Lee attacks in defense of AJ  

## Elimination Chamber Qualifier â€“ Reed vs Jey Uso vs El Grande Americano  
- Triple threat for final Elimination Chamber spot, WrestleMania stakes  
- Bronson Reed dominates with 330-pound power, worldâ€™s strongest slam  
- Americano hits big German suplex on Reed, then crashes on dive attempt  

## Reed Injured, Match Becomes One-on-One  
- Reed appears hurt (possible bicep/elbow), doctor checks ringside  
- Action shifts to extended Jey Uso vs El Grande Americano stretch  
- Both trade suplexes, superkicks, high-risk top-rope offense  

## Jey Uso Qualifies for Elimination Chamber  
- Sequence: superkick exchange, Americano kick, then Jey spear  
- Jey hits top-rope Uso Splash, pins Americano for three  
- Jey secures last Chamber spot, another WrestleMania title chance  

## AJ Styles Tribute, NASCAR Tie-In, European Tour  
- Cody Rhodes and others set for AJ Styles career celebration  
- Michael Jordanâ€™s NASCAR (Tyler Reddick) shown after Daytona, Atlanta wins  
- WWE announces May 31 event in France; tour hits Italy, Spain, France, Portugal, UK  

## Liv Morgan WrestleMania Decision Tease  
- Segment set for Liv to choose WrestleMania opponent  
- Womenâ€™s champs Stephanie Vaquer and Jade Cargill come out  
- Vaquer touts doing it alone; Cargill presented as dominant physical threat  

## Next Steps  
- Jey Uso heads to Elimination Chamber with WrestleMania hopes  
- Guntherâ€“AJ Stylesâ€“Dragon Lee issues likely continue  
- Liv Morganâ€™s final WrestleMania opponent choice still to be revealed
